Looking at the buggy code and trigger testcases, I can identify the issues:

1. In `put()`: When creating a new collection, `result` is set to `coll.add(value)`, but then if `coll.size() > 0`, `result` is set to `false`. This is incorrect - the return should indicate whether the value was added. The method should return the value itself (not null) when successfully added to a new collection.

2. In `putAll()`: Similar issue - when creating a new collection and adding values successfully, `result` is set to `false` after the map entry is created. This contradicts the intended return value showing whether any values were added.

The fix: Remove the lines that set `result = false` after adding to the map, as they incorrectly override the actual result of the add operation.

